 score along the edges of the trim.";i:35;s:32:"A picture would definitely help.";i:36;s:22:"Far away and close up.";i:37;s:83:"I would imagine that you need to end the chair rail just short of the stair nosing.";i:38;s:58:"And instead of cutting a square end return it to the wall.";i:39;s:63:"What this means is you cut a 45 angle on the end and then glue.";i:40;s:148:"The top of the top molding chair rail is at about 31 inches and given that the rail is extended a couple of inches from the wall it works just fine.";i:41;s:83:"The second picture is below in another reader comment by Kevin dated April 23 2013.";i:42;s:45:"He went with the molding below the hand rail.";i:43;s:54:"So you can see how this scenario may work out as well.";i:44;s:56:"How to do a chair railing on the stairs finish it first.";i:45;s:177:"Entering into the narrow hallway the palest of taupe paints above the dado rail and a chalky putty paint tone on the panelling below combine to set the tone for the whole house.";i:46;s:70:"Run a stud finder along the wall where the molding is to be installed.";i:47;s:37:"The problem came with the chair rail.";i:48;s:63:"On this project the top rail of the wainscot runs about 3 4 in.";i:49;s:30:"Above the top of the handrail.";i:50;s:85:"I start the layout by marking plumb lines for the end stiles of each run of wainscot.";i:51;s:47:"I then snap lines for the top and bottom rails.";i:52;s:70:"The point where the top rail intersects the landing panels plumb line.";i:53;s:56:"Before you begin wipe down your walls with a damp cloth.";i:54;s:76:"I installed a chair rail in our hallway before I added the Craftmold panels.";i:55;s:90:"I also laid out my panels to get a visual of how far or close I wanted my panel mouldings.";i:56;s:73:"Mark a level horizontal line where you want the top of your panels to go.";i:57;s:34:"Home chair rail molding up stairs.";i:58;s:56:"Ideas For Chair Rail Molding Up Stairs Written By Admin.";i:59;s:24:"Friday 5 June 2020 Edit.";i:60